25|$|Upon {{his trade}} to Miami, O'Neal began {{training}} {{to become a}} Miami Beach reserve officer. On December 8, 2005, he was sworn in, but elected for a private ceremony to avoid distracting attention from the other officers. He assumed a $1 per year salary in this capacity. Shortly thereafter, in Miami, O'Neal witnessed <b>a</b> <b>hate</b> <b>crime</b> (assaulting a man while calling out homophobic slurs) and called Miami-Dade police, describing the suspect and helping police, over his cell phone, track the offender. O'Neal's actions resulted in the arrest of two suspects on charges of aggravated battery, assault, and <b>a</b> <b>hate</b> <b>crime.</b>|$|E
