25|$|The Dirkhising {{case was}} {{repeatedly}} {{compared with the}} {{media coverage of the}} murder of Matthew Shepard although Dirkhising was a minor in a sex crime and Shepard's murder was <b>a</b> <b>hate</b> <b>crime</b> involving adults. Also the sexualities of the victims and attackers differed somewhat with Shepard being an openly gay man attacked by two heterosexual men, while Dirkhising's attackers were lovers and presumed to be gay.|$|E
25|$|Many discussions {{have focused}} on whether the attack should be {{described}} {{as an example of}} <b>a</b> <b>hate</b> <b>crime</b> and has been compared to the murder of the punk Brian Deneke in the United States. It has been widely perceived by goths as a more extreme example of the social intolerance, violence and abuse people can suffer {{as a result of their}} attachment to the goth subculture.|$|E
